<TITLE> Govt to import 1 lakh tonne wheat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 15 (bdnews24.com)  The government has decided to import one lakh tonne of wheat at the cost of Tk 330 crore through international tender. The cabinet committee on public purchase approved the proposal Thursday. The imported wheat will reach Bangladesh by June 30. Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam told reporters: "We'll import wheat from a country which will be able to supply the stuff in 45 days through participating in an international bidding." The government has set the shipment cost of the wheat at $450 per tonne for Chittagong port and $466 to reach up to Mongla port. The committee also approved a contract for appointment of consultants for development of the technical design for refurbishing and upgrading the Dhaka-Chittagong highway into four-lane motorway with world class facilities. The Asian Development Bank is providing 50 percent of the total project costs. LGRD adviser Anwarul Iqbal and food adviser AMM Shawkat Ali were also present in the meeting. bdnews24.
